ygData.msgSnippet: Salutations Beverly, Sorry about the slow response but things have been a bit wierd lately around here and I am way, way, way behind on my e-mail. Anyway,
ygData.messageBody:
Salutations Beverly,

Sorry about the slow response but things have been a
bit wierd lately around here and I am way, way, way
behind on my e-mail.

Anyway, wanted to throw in my welcome to you.

I have been on EQ close to four months now and I'm
afraid I'm addicted. I mostly play on the Xegony
server where my more or less only remains the 33rd lvl
wood elf Ranger Brangvyne Nimloth <Hand of Judgement>.
Bran can be found on for at least a while most
evenings, where she likes to sit among the trees and
work on her fletching skills, or go kill giants to
make money to work on her fletching skills. I finally
trived oak last night and immediately went out and
ruined my first attempt at an oak bow. I also made my
first True Shot Bow last night. :o)

I do have a lvl 2 half elf bard also named Brangvyne
on Cazic-Thule too although you can tell I obviously
don't get on her a lot.

I do love to chat though and can talk about almost
anything EQ or not. If you ever see my on pst . . .
:o)

I'm too little to group with you there, but I'd be
happy to say hi.

Hugs,
Bran

--- Beverly Koppersmith
